arn.description: The ARN that Amazon Route 53 assigns to the namespace when you create it.

description.description: The description that you specify for the namespace when you create it.

httpName.description: The name of an HTTP namespace.

name.description: The name of the http namespace.

tags.description: A map of tags to assign to the namespace. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
